  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A lot of people suffer from phobias. Phobias concerning certain diseases are not rare. This
      study will examine whether the COVID-19 (Coronavirus Disease) crisis was able to rise phobias
      in people and if those with preexisting phobias or fears were more likely to develop a phobia
      concerning COVID. It will look at different subtypes - physicians, medical staff, general
      public (not medically affiliated) and patients with psychiatric disorders.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
